      "blockId": "b9e9653b-6685-4bcd-a7d5-f427d15a97ab",
      "html": "Do you notice?<div><br></div><div>Notice how the 2010 OneNote is just full of colour.&nbsp;</div><div>Every section has its own colour.</div><div>It's subtle, but if you look closely, the entire section shares this single colour - the section tab, the pages pane, and then the content is overlaid on top. But there is a soft chrome around it that shows you visually you are inside the \"purple section\".</div><div><br></div><div>Modern OneNote has no such thing. Everything is a bland shade of gray. All the same.</div>",
      "deviceId": "f5eb80e6-baa8-4695-81f1-2195339b0c21",
      "timestamp": 1772334603351,
      "id": "9dcff3d9-ea01-491c-9899-1dae88c94f4f"
    },
    {
      "type": "block-update-html",
